Name: limb ischemia
Definition: An ischemia that is characterized by low blood supply to tissues in the limb due to interruption in the arterial blood supply.

Name: retinal ischemia
Definition: An ischemia that is characterized by restriction in blood supply to the retina.

Name: compartment syndrome
Definition: A vaginal adenoma that resembles the colorectal tubular adenoma.

Name: obsolete anaplastic childhood astrocytoma of brain
Definition: A vaginal adenoma that resembles the colorectal tubular adenoma.
Synonym: grade III pediatric astrocytoma of the brain
